&gt; Is anyone using Canoo WebTest for automated acceptance testing of web
&gt; applications?
&gt;
&gt; Having used HttpUnit and realized that it takes a lot of code to test
&gt; some basic assertions, the ability to drive HttpUnit with an XML file
&gt; sounds promising.  It&#39;s also an important step towards allowing
&gt; non-programmers (e.g. customers) to easily define acceptance tests.
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;m also interested because I&#39;m considering defining similar Ant tasks
&gt; for configuring JUnitPerf tests.  Something along the lines of:
&gt;
&gt;     &lt;timedTest id=&quot;1 second response time for something&quot;
&gt;         class=&quot;MyTestCase&quot; method=&quot;testSomething&quot; maxTime=100 /&gt;
&gt;
&gt;     &lt;loadTest id=&quot;10 user load test for something&quot;
&gt;         class=&quot;MyTestCase&quot; method=&quot;testSomething&quot; users=10 iterations=1
&gt; /&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Or applying decoration:
&gt;
&gt;     &lt;timedTest id=&quot;10 second response time for a 10 user load test&quot;
&gt; maxTime=10000&gt;
&gt;
&gt;         &lt;loadTest id=&quot;10 user load test for something&quot;
&gt;             class=&quot;MyTestCase&quot; method=&quot;testSomething&quot; users=10
&gt; iterations=1 /&gt;
&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/timedTest&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; This would alleviate having to programmatically configure various
&gt; performance tests, and allow non-programmers to define such tests.
&gt;
